Citations
Date: 1/11/1906
Source: Wanganui Herald
Author:
Vol / Page: 3
Edition:
Quote: TO-NIGHT the Vitoscope will show again, and as it is a show which is on the same high water mark of excellence as the best of the picture shows which have visited us, we can recommend our readers to patronise it.
Notes:

Date: 13/3/1911
Source: Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page: 8
Edition:
Quote: Workmen are busily engaged at present in the old Federal Billiard Saloon in Manners-street, renovating the historic hall and putting it in order for a picture theatre. Messrs. M'Mahon and Donelly have secured an extended lease of the building and propose to run a continuous all-day picture show.
Notes:

Date: 19/7/1910
Source: Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page: 7
Edition:
Quote: Another Picture Theatre. Sydenham ward of the city is to be provided with a permanent picture show, a syndicate having bought a building formerly used as a church, with a view to converting it into a theatre.
Notes:

Date: 26/9/1911
Source: Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page: 7
Edition:
Quote: Fire alarm at a Picture Show.... While 300 people were attending a show at a moving picture theatre a film ignited, and there was at once an outcry of "Fire!".
Notes:

Date: 9/1/1913
Source: Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page: 7
Edition:
Quote: A picture show hall in Nelson is advertised for sale.
Notes:

Date: 18/10/1911
Source: Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page: 4
Edition:
Quote: The Opera House is to be again opened as a permanent picture show.... This will again make three permanent moving picture establishments [in Palmerston North], and it is understood that there is a probability of a fourth picture hall being opened at an early date.
